<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-09-08T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-09-08T08:00:00-05:00" n="374" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d374">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">320/9–854: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d374fn1">Passed to <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>,
                                Sept. 8, 1: 30 p.m.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Manila</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-09-08T21:00:00+08:00">September
                                    8, 1954—9 p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Dulte 26. Department pass <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> NY
                            priority. For <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">Lodge</persName> from
                            Secretary. I believe we should get <persName corresp="#p_WWPWWKNB1">Wan</persName> elected if you can do it without open campaign which
                            could reasonably be interpreted as exertion of pressure. However, I
                            think you should check with latest views in Department as I am not up to
                            date.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                                </persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>